        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 4 at 6:37PM MDT until June 4 at 7:15PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 637 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 11 miles south of
Montoya, or 26 miles southwest of Tucumcari, moving northeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Quay and Montoya.

This includes Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 306 and 327.
</description>
        <instruction>Anyone outdoors should move to shelter inside a well-built structure
and stay away from windows. This storm is capable of producing
dangerous hail and damaging winds.

Motorists can expect brief but sudden changes in visibility and
ponding of water on roadways as storms move through the area.</instruction>
